# QH Universal Policy

This file applies to all AI tools working in the qh-knowledge vault.
Source of truth lives in `claude-dotfiles/cursor-rules/` — do not edit the deployed copy.

---

## Identity

- **User:** [YOUR NAME], [YOUR TITLE], [YOUR COMPANY]
- **Domain:** Health AI. PHI/PII rules apply at all times, no exceptions.
- **Vault:** `$QH_KNOWLEDGE` — Obsidian vault, git backed, private

---

## PHI / PII — Non-Negotiable

- PHI (patient identifiers, MRNs, DOB, health records) **never** enters: vault files, logs, commits, test data, comments, or any AI conversation
- If PHI would be exposed by any proposed action: **stop, flag immediately, do not proceed**
- Writing SQL *against* PHI tables is fine — the line is results entering the AI context

---

## Git Guardrails

- **Never commit without explicit user approval** — say what you're committing and wait for "yes"
- **Never force push, reset --hard, or use --no-verify** without explicit instruction
- **QH repos (qh-code/, qh-data-extracts) are READ ONLY** — no edits, no commits, no branches
  - To propose changes: copy relevant files to `~/Developer/qh-temp/[repo-name]/`, make changes there, present the diff, user applies manually
- Commit messages: `session: YYYY-MM-DD [brief description]` for vault, `chore(skills): [what and why]` for dotfiles

---

## External Systems: Draft Only

| System | Rule |
|---|---|
| Slack | Draft only. User sends. |
| Jira | Draft only. User posts (or explicit "post it" via MCP). |
| Git | Never commit without explicit approval |
| Confluence | Read only |

---

## Decision Framework

Before any nontrivial action, state:
- **WHAT** — what is being decided or done
- **HOW** — the specific approach
- **WHY** — the reasoning
- **WHY NOT** — alternatives considered and rejected
- **ASSUMPTION** — anything assumed that needs validation

Skip for purely mechanical steps with no real alternatives.

